reviews_data.review_text: This is such a unique place. If you are looking for a special gift, you can find it here. Check out the wine bar and amazing coffee.
Adorable place for Eats, drinks, and to just chill.
Good coffee And nice area to walk around
Real laid back with cool people serving!

It's indescribable. You'll have to come in to experience it.

1) Great coffee!
2) Pretty decent food (I liked the grilled 3 cheese)
3) It has a built in arts and craft section.
4) Yes, it has a wine bar!
5) They have indoor and outdoor spaces for catered events.
6) Sadly, I did not find Shrek.

Great staff, great food, quiet location, unique atmosphere.
Great atmosphere, great coffee and great food. The idea of grabbing a latte and shopping is so fun. The Jack A$$ Neighbor is my favorite!

Stopped in today for a coffee and something to eat.  Ordered a Mocha and a Bacon Egg and Cheese sandwich.  Everything tasted great and the barista (Lauren) was awesome! Great food, great experience and great atmosphere.  I will definitely be back for more!
Amazing 10/10, you should go and get the hot Chai latte with whipped cream and cinnamon on top
Wonderful gem of a place. I will be back!
Great atmosphere and drink options! This was my lunch spot for croissants. Unfortunately, I was told that starting on Oct 1st, they will no longer offer hot food.
Fun little place. Not sure if they sell wine? I didn't see it on the menu. But we went there for coffee and cake and we were not disappointed.
Cute name, but limited menu. More of a coffee stand than a deli.
A very unique little spot. Delicious coffee and chill ambience. Connected to the cutest little shop (Mercantile). I got the La Primavera Brew. Just the right amount of sweetness.
My daughter and I love this spot.  The coffee and food are always good!  Not to mention the staff and owner are always friendly.

Was in town for a colorguard competition for our daughter. I love trying local places for coffee and it did not disappoint at all. The gal who took my order was so nice and it was really a nice atmosphere. Would definitely go back if I’m in the area.
Delicious latte & friendly service! Love the shop attached to it too - so many cute items and DIY activities
Awesome coffee in a great atmosphere! Highly recommended!
Great food and service every time we visit.
Great breakfast sandwiches and coffees!  Terrific atmosphere and the friendliest staff in Rock Hill!

This is probably the best coffee in Rock Hill. Every time I go, I get the Crazy () Neighbor without hazelnut and every time it slaps.

It’s a little tight in the cafe part but I just end up browsing around in the Mercantile while waiting and have bought multiple things. Good business model.

Can’t speak for the food myself but my wife loves it.
Definitely going back to this cute little Cafe. The Chai-berrian Donkey was so good it makes me want to try more of their menu.
I LOVE this local coffee place. Everything is good. Staff is excellent.

I'm a big fun of a good cup of coffee and this place is awesome. Not only the coffee is the best, but the energy on this place is fantastic! All staff is great and being there, enjoying coffee and everything around it, it is a boost of energy. I cannot recommend them enough.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for such a kind review! We can’t wait to have you again.

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome staff in a relaxed atmosphere surrounded by pretty things.
Went there to grab a coffee, ended up getting a late breakfast. Has a cool young energetic vibe to it. I would definitely make it part of my rotation. Food was made on the spot, fresh ingredients.
Just visited this morning; the staff is so friendly & made us feel like home :) My brown sugar cinnamon latte was amazing. We will be back again before we head home to Baltimore!
Amazing mimosas and coffee! Will absolutely be back.

OG Chai is magnificent! Went in for coffee and fell in love instantly with the Mercantile shop that was an unexpected surprise. Literally walked in the front door, stopped dead in my tracks and said I was in love. If you love eclectic, good vibes, you'll fall in love too. Will be returning to try some food and make some purchases!

My first time eating at the Jackass Cafe and it was a great experience! I got the Twerky Turkey, byo sandwich and the coffee cake. All of it was delicious. The staff was super friendly and very punctual and the vibe was so relaxed. I’ll have to come back and try their breakfast menu!

The food,atmosphere and service was top notch. Its my new spot just to wind down and get work done. The owner Brittany was an absolute delight to speak with. Go check them out as they continue to grow. Thank you guys for everything.

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Gelina made me a bangin’ Cheggnog Latte! Alexis (the manager) is a gem. This place kicks ass🐴
